'''Ahmed Reda Tagnaouti''' ({{langx|ar|أحمد رضا التكناوتي}}; born 5 April 1996) is a Moroccan professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as [[goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Botola Pro]] club [[AS FAR]] and the [[Morocco national football team|Morocco national team]].

== Club career ==
On 30 March 2023, while still with [[Wydad AC]], Tagnaouti underwent a successful knee operation, having sustained an injury that saw him out of action for a prolonged period.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Erraji |first=Abdellah |title=Moroccan Goalkeeper Reda Tagnaouti Undergoes Successful Knee Operation |url=https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2023/03/354762/moroccan-goalkeeper-reda-tagnaouti-undergoes-successful-knee-operation |access-date=2023-03-30 |website=moroccoworldnews |language=en}}</ref>

== International career ==
Tagnaouti was part of Morocco's [[2018 African Nations Championship]] winning squad.

In May 2018, Tagnaouti was named in Morocco's 23-man squad for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/amp/football/441603882018|title=Boufal left out of Morocco squad}}{{dead link|date=September 2025|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> The following year Tagnaouti was selected for the [[2019 Africa Cup of Nations|2019]] [[Africa Cup of Nations]]. He also made the [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations|2021]] squad.

On 10 November 2022, he was named in Morocco's 26-man squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] in Qatar.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Morocco World Cup 2022 squad: Who's in and who's out? {{!}} Goal.com |url=https://www.goal.com/en-bh/lists/morocco-2022-world-cup-squad-hakimi-ziyech-mazraoui-qatar/blta36257fc4feeb66a |access-date=10 November 2022 |website=www.goal.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=10 November 2022 |title=Moroccan coach unveils list of 26 Atlas Lions in 2022 World Cup |url=https://en.hespress.com/52697-moroccan-coach-unveils-list-of-26-atlas-lions-in-2022-world-cup.html |access-date=10 November 2022 |website=HESPRESS English - Morocco News |language=en-US}}</ref> He and his teammates made history and became the first African nation in history to reach the semi-finals of the competition.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Walid Regragui avant d'affronter la France : 'Nous avons faim, nous voulons que l'Afrique soit au sommet du monde' |url=https://www.rtbf.be/article/walid-regragui-avant-d-affronter-la-france-nous-avons-faim-nous-voulons-que-l-afrique-soit-au-sommet-du-monde-11122333 |access-date=2025-07-19 |website=RTBF |language=fr}}</ref>

